                <note rend="inline" type="source">815.00/2670: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Minister in Honduras</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morales</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-08-28T19:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 28, 1923—7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Your 73, August 27, 10 a.m.</p>
                <p>The Department would be willing to consider a conference such as you suggest if
                    it were convinced that such a conference would be profitable. It does not,
                    however, perceive any advantage in holding a conference unless the Government of
                    Honduras is prepared to take such effective measures as will assure all parties
                    that the Government does not intend to impose a candidate in the forthcoming
                    elections. You will ascertain from President Lopez Gutierrez what measures the
                    Government is prepared to adopt should a conference such as you propose be
                    held.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
